<br>
High quality technical pens are also good for inking hair. Just use different sized pens and multiple strokes for varying width.<br>
<br>
I wouldn't recommend a crow quill for hair. Crow quills are a bit scratchy which is good for texturing, not hair. Also you need to hold them at a shallow angle for them to draw a line right which robs some control. Plus you can only pull the pen, and if you're a lefty like me, you've pushed pencils and pens all your life, pulling a crow quill feels strange.<br>
 <br>
But inking isn't everything. You need to be able to draw the hair well too. A good ink job on top of a poor drawing still looks like a bad drawing. <br>
<br>
